<ArkSwitch version="1.1.4">
  <!--
  *** Translation instructions ***
  
  1. Make a copy of this file, and name it "[LCID].xml", where [LCID] is a decimal (not hex!) locale number. See http://www.science.co.il/language/Locale-Codes.asp?s=decimal
  2. Change all the "value" attributes to contain your language's text. Make sure you keep all of the braced numbers: {0}, {1}, etc. !!!
  3. Copy the new XML file to your device, next to 1033.xml, and enjoy!
  
  NOTE: If your device's LCID is set improperly, or you wish to use a custom language, you may override ArkSwitch's detection by setting:
  [HKCU\Software\ARKconcepts\ArkSwitch]
  "OverrideLCID" = "12345" (this must be a string value type)
  -->
